    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Intrigue pg. 232</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 70 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 1 lb.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d3 (small), 1d4 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x2; <strong>Range</strong> 10 ft.; <strong>Type</strong> P or S; <strong>Special</strong> -</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Light; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Simple</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>This 4-inch blade is attached via a hinge to a wooden handle with a slot in the center, into which the blade can be folded. With a click of a switch, a spring thrusts the blade outward, where it locks into place until it is reset. Releasing the blade is a free action, and resetting it is a move action. The handle must be in your hand for the blade to be released; placing it in your hand requires the same type of action as drawing a weapon. A spring blade is easy to conceal: an observer must succeed at a DC 20 Perception check to notice the blade hidden within the wooden handle, and you gain a +4 bonus on Sleight of Hand checks to conceal a spring blade on your body.</p>",
